	    <![CDATA[
	    <div class="text-left well well-small" style="font-weight: normal;">
			<h2>Thank you for installing JoomBri Freelance</h2>
			<h4>What's new in v1.6 ?</h4>
		  	<ul>
		  		<li>Projects and users can save location information.</li>
		  		<li>Google Maps on Project detail page.</li>
		  		<li>Enhanced Project Search page.</li>
		  		<li>Embed YouTube link in Portfolios.</li>
		  		<li>Track the Project progress after awarding to Freelancer.</li>
		  		<li>Private Message included in Service progress update page.</li>
		  	</ul>
		  	<div class="alert alert-info alert-block">
				<h4>Create Menus!</h4>
				<p>If you are upgrading from earlier versions (prior to v1.5), you need to manually create two new menus <strong>My Services</strong> and <strong>Services Bought</strong> under JoomBri Menu. The above two menus are automatically created for new installation.</p>
			</div>
		  	<div class="alert alert-info alert-block">
				<h4>Disable Fields!</h4>
				<p>If you are upgrading from earlier versions (prior to v1.6), please disable <strong>(DO NOT DELETE)</strong> the custom fields related under Contact Information. The above fields are automatically created for new installation.</p>
			</div>
			<p><a href="http://www.joombri.in/features" target="_blank">Click here</a> for more features.</p>
			<p>Please visit <a href="http://docs.joombri.in/installation/change-log" target="_blank">Release Notes</a> to read the complete details.</p>
		</div>
	    ]]>
	</description>
	
